<p><em>Posted [2024:07:24:21:37:36] </em></p>=20
<p>So first you need a brief history lesson, my old profession did not real=
ly start with the awakening, or with the internet, or with cybernetics, or =
any other discovery. No those all played in to it, but my profession starte=
d on January 4th, 2000 when President Gore signed the SECURITY act. That bi=
ll required anyone who was awakened to register with the federal government=
, and provide regular updates on their location and employment. Which split=
 the burgeoning community of more abled into two camps, those the governmen=
t knew about, and those they did not. That second group suddenly found itse=
lf without legitimate means of employment, but with a suddenly enhanced mar=
ket position for committing crimes. No longer could a hacker decide to just=
 liberate a savings and loans institution of its surplus currency on a whim=
, if you were on the books they would find you, and if you weren=92t you be=
tter get good at it, since it is now your job.</p>=20
<p>And hire us they did, because in a world where only one in 50,000 has th=
e talent to begin with, its a lot easier to go on the offense and hire a he=
avy for a day, then to hire a straight for 10 years on the off chance your =
attacked.</p>=20
<p>Posted [2024:07:24:21:40:02]<br></p>=20
<p>So if you are a young person, with a lack of documentation, flexible mor=
als, and a Jordan Belfort esc desire to get rich, how do you start. Well fi=
rst you need a crew. One person working on their own is very unlikely to to=
 able to accomplish much beyond serving as target practice. Then you need t=
o find a fixer. This is the disreputable individual who will put you in con=
tact with you=92re employer. Said employer will then give you a job, and a =
you can either take it, not take it, or try and haggle them up on the price=
. And I recommend going hard on the second and third of those, there is not=
hing forcing you to take a job, and there is nothing forcing you to take a =
job at a bad price. </p>=20
<p>Posted [2024:07:24:21:43:56]<br></p>=20
<blockquote>Being aggressive with an employer seems like a great way to nev=
er get work again.</blockquote>=20
<p>Ya this is what I was talking about before, this movie crap. It is the e=
mployers literal job to haggle, and deal with the disappointment of teams b=
acking out on them. If they reacted to normal everyday business as a person=
al slight they will be out of a job in 6 months. Also while we are at it, i=
t is also not crucial that you are in the dark on the real entity that is p=
laying for your services. The crucial part is that no one can prove the com=
pany paid you, you figuring out who the company is, is irrelevant, and if y=
our employer is going to a lot of lengths to hide that, its a massive red f=
lag.</p>=20
<p>Which brings us to the final part of this, actually carrying out the job=
. First you need to plan heavily for how you are going to pull this off. Yo=
u advantage as the attacker is that your opponents don=92t know when and wh=
ere you are striking, so maximize that and figure out ahead of time where a=
nd when to go in. This isn=92t a fucking movie, people who go in and wing i=
t end up in jail, or dead, or dead in jail. </p>=20
<p>On a related note, shooting people like your Hans Gruber is also a terri=
ble idea. This isn=92t some 80s action vehicle, if you shoot someone in the=
 face that is murder. So unless for some terrible reason you have decided t=
o go after some third world military, or attack an Oracle Zero Zone, stick =
to the non-lethal options if you don=92t want all the 3 letter agencies try=
ing to give you a field colonoscopy.<br></p>=20
<p>Then once you have done the thing, you get to go back to get your money.=
 No there is this weird idea that this is when your employer is going to tr=
y and stiff you, which is insane. If they do that word will get out, and th=
ey will not be hiring anyone again. If they are going to fuck you over, the=
y are going to do it during the job. That said, best practice is to hold on=
to the item until the cash clears.</p>=20
<h2>Magic</h2>=20
<p><em>Willis Harman=92s Testimony to the Rehnquist Commission</em><br></p>=
=20
<p>What is magic? There are several things that this commission has asked m=
e to explain or illuminate today in the light of recent tragic events but t=
his seems to be the most fundamental. So what is magic? I could claim that =
its life, that its power, that its will and all of that is true, but as in =
many things my now deceased friend and colleague Michael Bertiaux put it be=
st with his 11 Commandments:</p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>Magic Comes from Focused Will</li>=20
<li>Magic is Fueled from Life</li>=20
<li>Magic Takes Effort equal to its effect by the efficiency to the 8th pow=
er</li>=20
<li>Magic Cannot Create more Life</li>=20
<li>Magic Cannot Create a Soul</li>=20
<li>Magic Cannot Manipulate Time</li>=20
<li>Magic Cannot Remove Matter from Reality</li>=20
<li>The Soul is Inherent to it=92s form, to Change it is to Destroy it</li>=
=20
<li>To Observe Something is to Change it</li>=20
<li>A Soul Once Destroyed Cannot be Restored</li>=20
<li>To Destroy the Soul is to Kill</li>=20
</ol>=20
<p>Any question you have is answered there. Can you bring back the dead? No=
, nor can you speak or commune with them. Can you go back in time? No, with=
 all respect to Marty McFly it=92s functionally impossible, as is going for=
ward or sideways, and attempts at prophesy or fortune telling also fail. Wh=
at about teleportation? Well our friends at the postal service can rest eas=
y because that to is beyond our keen. Well surely you say we can enchant an=
 object, a sword or a mirror, or even just a broom? Alas no object has a mi=
nd of it=92s own and without a mind to hold it the power just seeps away. A=
nd any attempt to ape Dr Frankenstein and make a golem, or to control other=
s minds, or any other trick best seen in a Hammer Horror Film also do not w=
ork. Even attempts to directly heal the sick often are not possible. The bo=
dy is a powerful thing, and while you can often restore something damaged, =
your body may well see Leukemia as working as intended. </p>=20
<p>Apart from those rules though, well you can do anything, if you have a d=
iscipline and the power. Move at impossible speeds, lift impossible objects=
, summon spirits to assist you, even Fly. Just don=92t ask me to read your =
mind. </p>=20
<h1>Savage Worlds Ruleset</h1>=20
<p>This is the demo ruleset for running this setting in savage worlds.</p>=
