<h2>Races</h2>=20
<p>The races in this setting represent which of the awakened options your c=
haracter has taken. Options are Hacker, Driver, Heavy, Mage, Summoner, Supe=
r, Regular.</p>=20
<h3>Hacker</h3>=20
<p><em>Where most people see the internet through screens and machines, you=
 see the internet by jacking in, or for the newer kids getting close enough=
 to a WIFI spot.</em></p>=20
<p>You are able to take the Hacking (Smarts) Skill. </p>=20
<p>You can take Hacker Edges</p>=20
<p>You have a derived stat 'Firewall', equal to 2 + Hacking/2</p>
<h3>Driver</h3>=20
<p><em>The average person these days relies on their car to drive itself, w=
here you tell 20 cars where to drive themselves. Not only can you control m=
ultiple devices at the same time, you can also jump into a specific device =
and pilot it like you were there, useful assuming your smarter then whateve=
r the lowest bidder wrote for the AI.</em></p>=20
<p>The total number of cars/drones/boats/devices you can control is theoret=
ically unlimited, but you can only give direction to a number of groups equ=
al to half your smarts die (so d6 is 3 groups)</p>=20
<p>You can also at any point jump into a specific device, in which case you=
 may now roll and take all checks for the vehicle using your own stats and =
wild die, at plus 1. </p>=20
<p>You can take Driver Edges</p>=20
<h3>Heavy</h3>=20
<p><em>Thanks to your awakening, your understanding of your own body has ne=
ver been greater. When normal men cannot handle cybernetics which boost pas=
t normal human potential you are able to use them without any issues.</em><=
/p>=20
<p>In combat deal two initiative cards to the Heavy, they act on both of th=
em taking full turns.</p>=20
<p>Outside of combat, all tasks and movement take half as much time.</p>=20
<p>You can take Heavy Edges</p>=20
<h3>Mage</h3>=20
<p><em>Your a Wizard Harry=85 Ya wont be the first or last time you hear th=
at, but being able to bend spacetime over your knee and make it cry uncle i=
s one hell of a consolation prize.</em></p>=20
<p>You are able to take the Spellcasting (Smarts) Skill.<em><br></em></p>=
=20
<p>You can take Mage Edges</p>=20
<h3>Summoner</h3>=20
<p><em>You feel like your people have gotten a bad rap. The ability to summ=
on and control creatures from beyond mortal keen has many uses, and the fac=
t that every representation in the media is necromancer this, warlock that =
is hurtful. Sometimes you also bring out old ones.</em></p>=20
<p>You are able to take the Summoning (Spirit) Skill.<em><br></em></p>=20
<p>You can take Summoner Edges</p>=20
<h3>Super</h3>=20
<p><em>Have you ever wanted to stop bullets with your hand, fold into a sui=
tcase, jump up 10 stories, make yourself invisible? Well all of those and m=
ore are possible if you can find your connection to the flow, and manifest =
it through your body. Just don=92t try all four of those at once, we are st=
ill cleaning up bits of Fred.</em></p>=20
<p>You are able to take the Flow (Spirit) Skill.<em><br></em></p>=20
<p>You can take Super Edges</p>=20
<h3>Regular</h3>=20
<p><em>You are just a normal person, no awakened powers. That said, no norm=
al person would survive in this business, so you clearly have some incredib=
le talents under the surface, that just required less invasive surgery.</em=
></p>=20
