<p> Each node can potentially have defensive software loaded on it. This is=
 split into software which will always go off when a hacker is either in th=
e node, or enters it (rare), and software that starting triggering once the=
 alarm goes off (common). Each piece of software is a power, from the hacke=
r powers list. It is casted using the hack skill of the system, with normal=
 modifiers from the difficulty, but no penalties from failing to cast. A no=
de cannot be a wildcard. </p>
<p>Certain powers generate noise, representing small errors and issues that=
 system security will eventually pick up on. Noise is associated with the n=
etwork of connected nodes that powers were used in. So if you cause noise i=
n a system connected to 10 other nodes, the noise builds up for all of them=
. At the start of each turn for each network, roll a D10, if the result is =
equal or less then the amount of noise currently in the network, add one no=
ise. If at the start of a turn the amount of noise is now 10, the alarm goe=
s off, alerting any whitehats on the system, and broader corporate security=
. Note that if you cut off a node from other nodes and split a network in h=
alf, both parts inherit 100% of the original noise, but noise is only gener=
ated after the power takes effect. So if I split the camera computer from t=
he broader network, it would still stay at 2 noise, if that was the level a=
t the start of the turn. But if cutting the system off generated 2 noise, t=
he systems that were linked before the power would not gain any.</p>
<h2>Powers - Hacker</h2>
<p>If you are a Hacker, this section details what powers you can use.</p>
<p>Your Arcane Skill is Hacking (Smarts). You start with the Control System=
 power, and two additional starting powers of your choice.</p>
<p>When you first use a power on a system you have to decide if you want to=
 go into a trance while hacking. If you do not, you are just using a device=
 screen, and have awareness of what is happening around you. If you go into=
 a trance you are fully in the system, and cannot see or notice things happ=
ening around your body. Each turn you are in a trance, you either decide to=
 go cool or hot. If you are running cool, you apply -5 to all noise generat=
ed by the power to a minimum of 0. If you are running hot, you take 4 separ=
ate actions a turn, drawing 4 separate cards if in combat.</p>
<p>When you use a power apply the modifier on the power to your roll. If yo=
u get a raise on the check, apply -5 to all noise generated by the power to=
 a minimum of 0. If you get a critical failure, the alarm on the network im=
mediately goes off.</p>
